    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "This message appears when I call `add_insecure_port('localhost:N')` presumably because `localhost` can resolve to ipv6 which Docker port forwarding is not friendly to.  Switching to a specifically ipv4 address like `127.0.0.1` prevents this error (but may or may not actually work).  A workaround would be to run your container with `--net=host` while developing locally.  Maybe worthwhile to examine your `/etc/hosts` in the container too.\r\n\r\nIf failure to bind the ipv6 address causes ipv4 binding to fail as well, that might be a GRPC bug, but it hasn't been proven here yet."
  },
